{
  "stem": "868.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We don't speak Italian, because we were born in France and raised in-- in France.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that's why French was speaking-- spoken at-- spoken at home.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And that's why we don't [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] speak Italian fluently.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We were given fake names immediately, Capaldi.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I became Nicola Capaldi.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "My brother was Francesco.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And there was one other boy there, Jewish boy, who also had been caught at the cinema.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But he managed, in the confusion and in the hysteria of the moment, to quickly make his way up to the balcony where the seats had been stashed.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he hid under the seats.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And he waited till everybody was gone, and then found his way, also, to the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So now, there the three of us, all Capaldis, all related, all with the same story.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we started living in that orphanage all through-- we're now November, the day after the raid, November 7, 1943-- all through until the liberation of Florence.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] We were never compromised, mainly because Don Giovanni, after having secured a safe place in that orphanage, went back and took care of all the other Jewish refugees who were-- who had escaped this raid, who had managed not to be caught.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the reason he was in charge now was that Don Casini, the original supervisor of all these clandestine operation, had been seized by the Gestapo and was held at the Murate prison in Florence.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that Don Giovanni took over the responsibility, which was enormous.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were still hundreds.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But he came to visit us occasionally, always inquiring about our well-being.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "While in-- at the Varlungo convent, he was concerned with the women that were hidden there.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
